    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes a copy-paste error in `sm90_bf16_k_grouped_gemm` where `SM100ArchSpec` was incorrectly used instead of `SM90ArchSpec` for TMA descriptor block size calculations.\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nIn `csrc/jit_kernels/impls/sm90_bf16_gemm.hpp`, the function `sm90_bf16_k_grouped_gemm` (lines 259-274) was using `SM100ArchSpec` to calculate block sizes for TMA descriptors:\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\nSM100ArchSpec::get_ab_load_block_m(...)\r\nSM100ArchSpec::get_ab_load_block_n(...)\r\nSM100ArchSpec::get_cd_store_block_m(...)\r\nSM100ArchSpec::get_cd_store_block_n(...)\r\n```\r\n\r\nSince this file is the SM90 (Hopper) implementation, it should use `SM90ArchSpec` consistently, like all other functions in the same file (`sm90_bf16_gemm`, `sm90_m_grouped_bf16_gemm_contiguous`, `sm90_bf16_m_grouped_gemm_masked`, etc.).\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\n\r\nReplace all `SM100ArchSpec` references with `SM90ArchSpec` in the `sm90_bf16_k_grouped_gemm` function.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\nThis change affects block size calculations for TMA descriptors on SM90 GPUs. The fix ensures consistent architecture-specific behavior matching the function's intended target (SM90/Hopper).\r\n\r\nFixes #242",
